1

00:00:02,570  -->  00:00:06,465
If you dive back into the models we fit using Scikit-learn,

2

00:00:06,465  -->  00:00:08,790
you'll notice we didn't get as much information back,

3

00:00:08,790  -->  00:00:11,700
regarding the coefficients in terms of the p-values.

4

00:00:11,700  -->  00:00:13,725
Even if you pulled the coefficients,

5

00:00:13,725  -->  00:00:17,580
they don't actually match what was retrieved using the statsmodels library.

6

00:00:17,580  -->  00:00:19,980
The shift from statistics to machine learning,

7

00:00:19,980  -->  00:00:23,595
is one in which we care less about the relation of the inputs to the output,

8

00:00:23,595  -->  00:00:28,710
and one where we care about predicting the output correctly regardless of the input.

9

00:00:28,710  -->  00:00:30,660
The Scikit-learn library is one of

10

00:00:30,660  -->  00:00:33,945
the most popular machine learning libraries and therefore,

11

00:00:33,945  -->  00:00:35,235
the tools in this library,

12

00:00:35,235  -->  00:00:38,020
are just aimed at the second point.
